> Win 7 *Ultimate* upgrade 

All the Windows 7 versions are the same in terms of installation, but 
which version you receive is decided by the serial number.  You can 
"upgrade" by changing the serial number to that of Ultimate: 

Highlight Computer (desktop or start menu)
Right click
Properties

Windows Activation
"Change Product Key"

The question though is, apart from the drivers, what other crapware, 
sampleware, dodgy antivirus, useless applications, etc have HP 
pre-installed? 

It might be as well to start with a wipe and reinstall of only the stuff 
you actually want -- but if you do, make sure you have at least the 
network drivers downloaded to another partition or to (unzipped) to a DVD 
or CD.  If you have at least those, all the others you can get from the HP 
site and install them online.


